English Premier League club Chelsea, has announced that it has parted ways with Italian manager Antonio Conte, after two seasons in charge. JOHANNESBURG - English Premier League club Chelsea, has announced that it has parted ways with Italian manager Antonio Conte, after two seasons in charge. Conte won the Premier League title in his first season in charge which was the London club’s sixth league title in it’s history. Despite a difficult second season which saw Chelsea fail to finish in the top four places and miss out on Champions League qualification, the Italian did manage to win the FA Cup in what was his last game in charge at the club. In a statement the club thanked and wished Conte the best of luck in his future endeavors. 